ng the integration of NMR with other techniques and the development of new pulse sequences.'", "The paper titled 'NMR application in unconventional shale reservoirs – a new porous media research frontier' with the given abstract could be cited in the paper: 'A review on the applications of nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) in the oil and gas industry: laboratory and field-scale measurements'."), 70: ("There is a paper. Title: 'Pulsed nuclear magnetic resonance studies of porosity, movable fluid, and permeability of sandstones'. Abstract: 'Pulsed nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) is used to study porosity, movable fluid, and permeability of sandstones. The NMR measurements provide relaxation time distributions that are correlated with pore size and fluid saturation. The movable fluid fraction is estimated from the NMR signal. Permeability is estimated from the relaxation times using empirical correlations. The study establishes the basis for using NMR in petrophysical evaluation of sandstones.'", "The paper titled 'Pulsed nuclear magnetic resonance studies of porosity, movable fluid, and permeability of sandstones' with the given abstract could be cited in the paper: 'A review on the applications of nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) in the oil and gas industry: laboratory and field-scale measurements'."), 71: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 72: ("There is a paper. Title: 'Porosity distributions in carbonate reservoirs using low-field NMR'. Abstract: 'None'", "The paper titled 'Porosity distributions in carbonate reservoirs using low-field NMR' with the given abstract could be cited in the paper: 'A review on the applications of nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) in the oil and gas industry: laboratory and field-scale measurements'."), 73: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 74: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 75: ("There is a paper. Title: 'Application of nuclear magnetic resonance permeability models in tight reservoirs'. Abstract: 'Nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) permeability mo