ing (MRI) and relaxation time measurements to evaluate polymer flooding in core samples. MRI provides spatial maps of oil and water saturation during the flood. Relaxation time measurements provide information on fluid-pore interactions. The results show that polymer flooding recovers more oil than water flooding, especially from heterogeneous regions. The MRI and NMR data provide insights into the mechanisms of polymer flooding at the pore scale.'", "The paper titled 'Polymer flooding enhanced oil recovery evaluated with magnetic resonance imaging and relaxation time measurements' with the given abstract could be cited in the paper: 'A review on the applications of nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) in the oil and gas industry: laboratory and field-scale measurements'."), 122: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 123: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 124: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 125: ("There is a paper. Title: 'Experimental investigation on CO 2 injection in block M'. Abstract: 'None'", "The paper titled 'Experimental investigation on CO 2 injection in block M' with the given abstract could be cited in the paper: 'A review on the applications of nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) in the oil and gas industry: laboratory and field-scale measurements'."), 126: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 127: ('[NOTEXIST]', '[NOTEXIST]'), 128: ("There is a paper. Title: 'Pulsed-field gradient nuclear magnetic resonance as a tool for studying translational diffusion: Part 1. Basic Theory'. Abstract: 'None'", "The paper titled 'Pulsed-field gradient nuclear magnetic resonance as a tool for studying translational diffusion: Part 1. Basic Theory' with the given abstract could be cited in the paper: 'A review on the applications of nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) in the oil and gas industry: laboratory and field-scale measurements'."), 129: ("There is a paper. Title: 'Pulsed field gradient stimulated echo methods for improved NMR diffusion measurements in heterogeneous systems'. Abstract: 'None